race.comment: SNEAKILY (6) will find this a little easier than her second on debut six-and-a-half weeks ago, beaten 2.25 lengths at the end of 1609m at Ellis Park (Turf). Will benefit from that experience so a big run is anticipated. ATLANTIC BEACH (10) started at big odds on debut last start when fourth, beaten a head, over 1408m at Woodbine. Sure to improve and can get off the mark this time. TURNER'S CHARM (1) made an encouraging debut last time out, finishing 0.8 lengths from the winner in second over 1408m at Kentucky (Turf). Improver with a solid top-three chance. TRUST ACCOUNT (5) ran a fair race on debut last time out, beaten 5 lengths into fourth over 1609m at Ellis Park (Turf) on August 18. Among the better hopes. Something for the Multiples: GINGER ALE (2)
